		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's a post about the GG and Capcom games (with special NSFs for those games <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" />)
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=7186">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=7186</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />It had to do with the music driver in Capcom's games from ~1989-1990.  The version at this time didn't set the sweep registers, while the Game Genie mucked around with said registers.

		

